Content:: Luis Omedes (12 January 1938 – 18 July 2022) was a Spanish sportsman. He competed in the men's coxed four event in the rowing at the 1952 Summer Olympics.[1] He also competed in the men's singles in the luge at the 1968 Winter Olympics.[1]  This biographical article relating to Spanish rowing is a stub.
